    <abstract>
      <t>To prevent WebRTC applications, such as browsers, from launching attacks by sending traffic to unwilling victims, periodic consent to send needs to be obtained from remote endpoints.

 This document describes a consent mechanism using a new Session Traversal Utilities for NAT (STUN) usage.</t>
